creator: ACS Technologies
descriptionHtml:
Connect with what’s going on at your church anytime. Contact your small groups, coordinate group activities, RSVP to church events and meetings, manage your giving, update your information, and more.

// This app is only for people who attend a church that is using Realm Connect—the app-enabled version—for its church's administration, finances, and community. Please check with your church staff before connecting. //

CONNECT WITH YOUR CHURCH COMMUNITY
• Post messages or prayer requests to a group newsfeed
• Add comments to messages and events
• Share photos of your ministry activities
• Communicate with your church groups throughout the week

KEEP EVENT DETAILS AT YOUR FINGERTIPS 
• RSVP to group or church-wide events
• Sign up to bring items to an event
• See who is attending and who can't make it 
• Add comments to events 

ABOUT
Realm is a church ministry tool designed and developed by ACS Technologies. It connects your entire church and personalizes everyone’s involvement in your ministry. This app fully integrates with your church’s Realm database and is included with your Realm Connect subscription at no additional charge.
descriptionShort: Connect with your church in amazing new ways.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
Volunteers and organizers can connect with their teams!

In the Serving section volunteers can:

· View and manage serving preferences, skills and interests

· View serving team information such as current roles and other serving opportunities

Volunteers can create posts and share photos on the team Newsfeed. Organizers can also create a chat and send Inbox messages.

Add an online meeting link to events. If your groups are meeting online, you can add a meeting URL.

Bug fixes.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
Check in with the Connect app. Use your mobile device to check yourself and your family in.


If you need to stop by a kiosk for an in-person event, you’ll receive a check-in code within the app. Scan the code to complete check-in and print your badge.


If you’re attending a virtual event, you can see the event’s details and join the event from your mobile device.


Mark attendance with more detail. You can now mark whether individuals attended an event in-person or virtually.

ABOUT

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
Parent/Guardian Oversight is now available! When this feature is enabled for a group, parents and guardians can:
- View a list of their children’s groups
- View and respond to content from their children’s group on their newsfeed
- View and respond to their children’s inbox messages
- View a roster of parents and guardians participating in a group
- Customize notification settings for their children’s groups
